00057 /**
00058  * \ingroup ExodusFileIO
00059  * \brief Struct hold info about the file format for dataset.
00060  *
00061  * \description
00062  *
00063  *    Need to keep exoid
00064  *
00065  *    It would be more aesthetically pleasing to put the vertIDs
00066  *    in each mesh, but if put here, it is easier to manage 
00067  *    cleaning up the dynamic memory.
00068  *
00069  * \modifications
00070  *    - 8/01/2005 WSD Created.
00071  */
00072 typedef struct {
00073   int cpu_word_size;
00074   int io_word_size;
00075   int exoid;
00076   int numTotalVert; /**< number of global vertices */
00077   int numMesh;      /**< the number of meshes */
00078   int** vertIDs;    /**< for each mesh, the global vertex IDs (index by
00079                  local ID) */
00080 } _FC_DsExodusIOInfo;
00081 
00082 /**
00083  * \ingroup ExodusFileIO
00084  * \brief Struct hold info about the file format for mesh.
00085  *
00086  * \description
00087  *
00088  *    Holds indexing information
00089  *
00090  *    NOTE: We also keep the mesh's Exodus ID, but this is stored up a level on
00091  *    the mesh's fileInfo object so that it can be retained when writing to a
00092  *    different file.
00093  *
00094  * \modifications
00095  *    - 9/01/2005 WSD Created.
00096  */
00097 typedef struct {
00098   //int blkid;   /**< exodus ID for the block */
00099   int meshID;  /**< id to look up vertIDs in dsIOInfo */
00100   int elemOffset; /**< Offset into global element numbering 
00101                   (elemID + offset = global) */
00102 } _FC_MeshExodusIOInfo;
00103 
00104 /**
00105  * \ingroup ExodusFileIO
00106  * \brief Struct hold info about the file format for subset.
00107  *
00108  * \description
00109  *
00110  *    Need to keep node block id & association.
00111  *    NOTE: Only side sets are read lazily -- it's easier (spacewise) to 
00112  *    just do the node sets during initial read.
00113  *
00114  * \modifications
00115  *    - 8/08/2005 WSD Created.
00116  */
00117 typedef struct {
00118   int assoc_flag;  /**< 0 = node, 1 = side, 2 = elem */
00119   int nsssid;      /**< exodus ID for the node set/side/elem set */
00120 } _FC_SubExodusIOInfo;
00121 
00122 /**
00123  * \ingroup ExodusFileIO
00124  * \brief Struct hold info about the file format for variable
00125  *
00126  * \description
00127  *
00128  *    Need to keep type of var and it's index. global vars
00129  *    cannot be read lazily.
00130  *
00131  * \modifications
00132  *    - 9/02/2005 WSD Created.
00133  *    - 9/09/2007 ACG added attrIndex for basic var. I think
00134  *                this really could just use the varIndex since
00135  *                we know otherwise if its a seq or basic var
00136  *                (note that FC_AT_WHOLE_MESH is not an attr).
00137  *                Probably could even drop this if didn't
00138  *                do lazy loading
00139  */
00140 typedef struct {
00141   char varType[2]; /**< "n" for nodal, or "e" for element */
00142   int varIndex;    /**< exodus index (starts from 1) */
00143   int attrIndex;    /**< exodus index (starts from 1) */
00144 } _FC_VarExodusIOInfo;
